{{about|the music event|the film festival|Berlin International Film Festival}} {{Infobox music festival | name =Berlin Festival | image =Berlin Festival 2011 2.jpg | caption = | location =[[Berlin Tempelhof Airport]] | years_active =2005-present | founders = | dates = | genre = [[Electronic dance music]], rock | attendance = | capacity = | website =[http://www.berlinfestival.de/en.html Berlin Festival] - official site }}
'''Berlin Festival''' is a two-day outdoor rock/ electro music event which is located near the city of [[Berlin]], Germany at the former airfield '[[Berlin Tempelhof Airport]]' which is now a community park.<ref name="official">http://www.berlinfestival.de/ Berlin Festival</ref> It was first organized in 2005, since then, its audience has grown to about 20,000 visitors. [[Berlin]] Festival was awarded 'Best European Festival Line-Up' at the [[European Festivals Awards]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eu.festivalawards.com/latest/and-the-winners-are-3/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007141112/http://eu.festivalawards.com/latest/and-the-winners-are-3/ |archivedate=2014-10-07 |df= }}</ref>
Usually, the festival takes place in September. The organisators announced that they will take a "creative break" in 2016.<ref name="official" />
