A '''continuing trespass''' is: *a [[wrongful act]] involving a course of action which is a direct [[invasion]] of the [[rights]] of another.<ref>52 [[American Jurisprudence|Am. Jur.]], Trespass § 18</ref> *a [[trespass]] in the taking of goods, although without intent to appropriate them, followed by an [[:wikt:appropriation|appropriation]], the original trespass being deemed to continue to the time of the appropriation, so that the subsequent appropriation is [[larceny]].<ref>State v. Coombs, 55 Me. 477 (Maine 1868).</ref>
